text: was a town located in Atetsu District, Okayama Prefecture, Japan. As of 2003, the town had an estimated population of 3,922 and a density of 32.35 persons per km². The total area was 121.25 km². On March 31, 2005, Ōsa, along with the towns of Shingō, Tessei and Tetta (all from Atetsu District), was merged into the expanded city of Niimi. Category:Dissolved municipalities of Okayama Prefecture
title: Ōsa, Okayama
